    {
      "topic": "AI/GenAI breakthroughs November 9-23, 2025 major research labs",
      "title": "AI Scientific Breakthroughs 2025: Gemini 3, AlphaFold Oncology Wins & More - Dana Love",
      "url": "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGeBZ94dmxUZWazUPZPCyBP5ET-I332z-Q9KGuPl0wZUUtu_SlIcRFE9M9jxmP5WflE0eFcDssojx0_1xYTbUDiR3GTDuu2aVaVrEinzem9Ri9Ftu9-kcJ6y-fNgCJ-I_s7qwtNpN1yeISbmmsip12BzA==",
      "uuid": "e1f2b3c4-d5e6-7a8b-9c0d-1e2f3a4b5c6d",
      "summary": "Google introduced Gemini 3 on November 18, 2025, a multimodal AI model capable of natively processing text, images, video, audio, and code, leading major reasoning benchmarks with new features like a 'Deep Research mode' for scientific investigations. Concurrently, Isomorphic Labs, a DeepMind spinout, advanced AlphaFold 3-designed oncology candidates into human trials, demonstrating atomic-accuracy prediction of protein-ligand interactions. Fully autonomous agent systems are now conducting complete research cycles in various labs, outperforming human graduate students in biomedical tasks. Furthermore, hybrid quantum-classical AI systems are showing significant speedups in simulating molecular interactions for applications such as battery materials and drug binding. These advancements highlight AI's transition from an assisting role to a leading force in scientific discovery, creating opportunities for decentralized compute, tokenized IP, and verifiable data provenance, especially at the intersection of AI and blockchain."
    },
    {
      "topic": "New AI models and algorithms released November 2025 OpenAI Google DeepMind Meta Anthropic",
      "title": "AI Scientific Breakthroughs 2025: Gemini 3, AlphaFold Oncology Wins & More - Dana Love",
      "url": "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGeBZ94dmxUZWazUPZPCyBP5ET-I332z-Q9KGuPl0wZUUtu_SlIcRFE9M9jxmP5WflE0eFcDssojx0_1xYTbUDiR3GTDuu2aVaVrEinzem9Ri9Ftu9-kcJ6y-fNgCJ-I_s7qwtNpN1yeISbmmsip12BzA==",
      "uuid": "f2g3h4j5-k6l7-8m9n-0o1p-2q3r4s5t6u7v",
      "summary": "Google released Gemini 3 on November 18, 2025, establishing new standards in multimodal reasoning by natively processing text, images, video, audio, and code in a single pass. This model now holds top positions on major reasoning benchmarks, including Humanity’s Last Exam, GPQA Diamond, and Video-MMMU. Gemini 3's new Deep Research mode enables planning multi-step scientific investigations, tool utilization, and result verification. In related breakthroughs, Isomorphic Labs, a DeepMind spinout, has successfully used AlphaFold 3 to design several oncology candidates that are now entering human clinical trials, predicting protein-ligand interactions with atomic precision. Autonomous agent systems in various research labs are also closing the loop on scientific discovery, running full research cycles, from hypothesis generation to experimentation and iteration, without human intervention. The article suggests these AI scientific breakthroughs, alongside quantum-AI hybrids, present significant opportunities for blockchain integration in areas like decentralized computing and tokenized intellectual property."
    },
    {
      "topic": "Academic conference proceedings AI/GenAI November 9-23, 2025",
      "title": "GenAI Conference @ The Open University UK - Eurocall",
      "url": "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEa354CyrFKu_v3FKZV8Gl6CkPe5AJq3W_grJOcuy6MBLHSNL56uyWErkuIS80lgFYHNnlmEz0m7EDx4fqygWN0VrbNs-W8VeGTC87ZAORsWCksOvXnd2IIlJxAhhqY61kXpxOj4JcvkXMyaeg_MqbdZSuR8ncDEL55UcU_We9pfqKw8ZPAJg==",
      "uuid": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7g8h-9i0j-1k2l3m4n5o6p",
      "summary": "The GenAI Conference, a hybrid event, is scheduled for November 13th and 14th, 2025, at The Open University UK. Organized by Eurocall, this conference focuses on 'Shifting Power in Language Learning and Applied Linguistics with GenAI,' exploring the ethical and responsible integration of AI in language and culture education and applied linguistics. The event aims to discuss how AI can empower learners and reshape the dynamic between educators and students. Key topics include AI's impact on educator roles, its potential for inclusive and personalized learning, ethical and sustainability challenges in AI integration, and theoretical frameworks guiding AI in applied linguistics and language learning. The conference will feature keynote speakers such as Prof. Clare Wright, Prof. Kate Borthwick, and Dr. Tracie Farrell, along with an expert panel, and offers both in-person and online session formats for presentations and facilitated discussions."
    },
    {
      "topic": "General AI/GenAI progress healthcare applications November 9-23, 2025",
      "title": "Generative AI in clinical (2020–2025): a mini-review of applications, emerging trends, and clinical challenges - Frontiers",
      "url": "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEcJgKd8qVWfwR15pgs6bt--kF1_18ThJhp5DgtASFfjRiIJH5YAnE1_qXfZQUnZggONvezZ4T4SE7LDBLZ2NEQ-fRaQEMPKazEaVE0VgzFZwp1hWg56wVI5uwEPdtgRi5a7D_cU1O4J5SIf_aOagJSPdFq016flijXRH5cFHMXQ_dZ5MZQzxErdX4dzBLVpDewVehPFfW2",
      "uuid": "p9q8r7s6-t5u4-3v2w-1x0y-z9a8b7c6d5e4",
      "summary": "A mini-review published on November 3, 2025, in Frontiers in Digital Health, analyzes the progress of Generative AI (G-AI) in clinical applications between 2020 and 2025, identifying three key trends: data augmentation for limited datasets, automation of expert tasks, and generation of new biomedical knowledge. The review highlights that G-AI, including GANs, diffusion models, and Vision-Language Models (VLMs), is actively used in radiology, dermatology, genetics, and drug discovery. While image-centric applications dominate, narrative (EHR) and molecular design domains are rapidly expanding. Despite demonstrated accuracy gains, challenges persist, such as synthetic data overlooking rare pathologies, multimodal systems hallucinating clinical facts, and the amplification of demographic biases. The article emphasizes the need for robust validation, interpretability techniques like StylEx, and strong governance frameworks to ensure safe and ethical integration of G-AI into routine healthcare practices, ensuring transparent reasoning and addressing bias propagation."
    }
  ],
  "summary_done": true
}

